<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Grandjean, who created the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Aphelacaridae" genus="Aphelacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Aphelacarus</taxonomicName>
, designated 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Parhypochthoniidae" genus="Parhypochthonius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinus">Parhypochthonius acarinus</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Aphelacaridae" genus="Aphelacarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acarinus">Aphelacarus acarinus</taxonomicName>
] as the type. According to the classification recently proposed by him (Grandjean, 1954a) the genus is the single representative of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aphelacarinae">Aphelacarinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
